review_blob: My favorite Bells brew. I love it, I nearly lived in the cafe when it came back for a few weeks earlier this winter.

Whew! While I do like this more than the original Arrogant Bastard as well as Double Bastard, I think the Oaked aspect of this is over marketed. I was really wishing for a quick hint of scotch or whiskey before the wonderful bitter beatdown came on. Still awesome though.

Ahhhhh! I love this beer! It is so light and crisp and still has the flavor to keep you interested! Its pleasant aroma is inviting and while in your mouth you will get a succession of interesting flavors. Its really quite a good one!
So-so on this one. The look of the beer in its glass is more appealing than the actual taste. Leagues above similar priced beer such as Heiniken or Becks.

At least it has a nice color to it. Other than that pretty boring. I do rather enjoy getting a 12 pack and watching friends think theyre getting wild drunk off of it while they think its something in a class above Becks...not even any alcohol in this really!
Well, how the fuck is this even beer? How does this have a massive following? Im completely lost. 1 dollar a pint is very convincing though. I joined this party for a night.

Nothing special about this beer. Designed purely for getting straight up nasty on. Its great or is it horrible? It doesnt taste like a good beer. Its not a good beer. Sure tastes like a fucking beer though!! Best served ice cold in a large glass pitcher at your local dive.
Well...it looks very nice in a glass, but Im afraid I consider this to be a very boring beer. Nothing exciting in the taste...Im sure this was a great beer back in 1830 or whatever the hell.
Pours well, thin head, really pleasant aroma! Taste is smooth and a rather complex lingering palate. One of the better red ales I know of.
Not too heavy, not too light, excellent variation of flavors on the palate. Fruity, wheat, and spice. Very delicious. Nice and cloudy. Recommendable.

Amazingly spiced. I could go on repeating what everyone else has said about the spicy malt finish and blah blah blah but you know what...it doesnt matter this beer is great and gets you loose after a pint.
Intense bitterness with a pleasant aftertaste. 750ml bottle purchased in Kalamazoo @ TIffanys. Who knows how long its been on their shelf. Im satisfied with this.
Has to be in my top favorite beers of all time.  Love it mixed with Guinness...amazing raspberry flavor is strong but no overpowering. Expensive but worth it!
Not my favorite stout by any means...tasty none the less. Would enjoy more if chocolate was more present. The aftertaste to me is a bit metallic almost. Definitely worth a try.
Very heavy and thick almost like eating a loaf of bread. Very enjoyable strong flavors of coffee and licorice (most present). Pours a very pretty pitch black colour.
Wow. This beer had an amazing aroma as soon as I popped the cork, flowers and hops. The taste is great and leaves a nice aftertaste...pours beautiful dark gold with a nice white head.
BLANK this beer tastes like water. i dont get it. is this a joke? waste of money and boring in my mouth.
I thought this beer was very tasty. 650ml bottle bought at Tiffanys Kalamazoo. Drank out of frosty mug. Really love the smooth roasted nut flavor. I reccomend this for sure.

I very much enjoy this beer. Its very very light and goes great with any kind of meal in my opinion. Its not a really amazing brew but its just so mild and smooth I find it becoming a reliable selection for any night.

I come from this beers hometown. Everybody here goes wild for it when it comes out. Im not such a hardcore fan, Bells has better to offer. However, this is a good one to grab for a change. Its not too heavy and its crisp. Great for a BBQ or a day at the beach.

Its refreshing. I like it because its cheap, in everystore, and almost always cold. As far as having any characteristics of a beer lovingly crafted by anybody who cares...its got none. Thats not its style.
Not as much cherry flavour as I was expecting but I wasnt dissapointed. Very tasty and enjoyable. A bit expensive but still well worth it in my opinion.
One of my favorite beers of all time. Chocolate coffee caramel beer is the deScription I give my friends who are interested in trying it. All love it unless they dislike coffee.
Super bubbly! Very light in the mouth with a really crisp aftertaste. Good beer but I doubt Ill shell out the bucks for it again. Glad I tried it.
Beatiful colour and head from bottle pour. Delicious flavour love the lambic touch. Could this beer be anymore delicious?
Amazing. My favorite of the rouge brews without a doubt. Beautiful color and delicious aroma. I really enjoy the citrus and spiciness of this beer.

I really enjoyed this beer. Poured from the bottle with a huge frothy white head just like in the picture. Its rather dry but it is complimented by the sweet fruit tastes. Makes me interested in other Delirium brews.
Very fitting for the winter months. Poured from a bottle; nice head and aroma. All around a sweet beer that pleases to the end of your glass. Keeps you nice and warm too.

Not the beat oatmeal stout but still good. Pours a nice colour and without too much head from the bottle. Nice aroma. This beer isnt retired but it has been relabled. I reccomend it to fans of any kind of stout.

Bottle out of six pack, pours amazing dark colour. Beautiful tan head. Smooth and tasty to the finish with a huge array of flavours almost too many to taste. Also a very pleasant aroma. Im happy my home town has such a wonderful beer named after it.
